President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Richard K. Bell as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Republic of Cote D’Ivoire. Bell is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and currently serves as Charge d’Affaires of the American Embassy in N’Djamena, Chad. He has had previous assignments as a foreign policy advisor to the United States Africa Command in Germany, Deputy Chief of Mission at the United States Embassy in Niger, and head of the Political and Economic Affairs Section of the United States Embassy in Denmark. Bell has also served in Iraq and has received numerous awards for his work. He speaks French and Arabic.

President Donald J. Trump has also announced his intent to appoint Charles M. Wooley as a Commissioner (Government Representative) of the Great Lakes Fishery Commission. Wooley is from Ohio.